From John Werner Subject Re Help with antidepressants In article Gordon Taylor wrote The Prozac gave very bad anxiety jitters and insomina it was impossible to sit still for more than a minute or I tried Prozac a few months ago and had some insomnia from it but no anxiety or I probably could have lived with the insomnia if the Prozac had done any good but it only provided a tiny Maybe because the person who prescribed it didn't know much and gave up after a dose didn't Now I'm seeing a psychiatrist who has put me on Zoloft another serotonin reuptake inhibitor like Prozac One pill day seemed to help Now I'm trying Zoloft has fewer and milder side effects than I think my doctor said that only of the people taking Zoloft have to discontinue it because of side The only problem I'm having is some minor GI distress but nothing too Hopefully the Zoloft will Maybe your friend should try this one My psychiatrist's strategy seems to be to first try one of the serotonin drugs usually If that works If it works but has too many side effects try Zoloft or maybe If the serotonin drugs don't work at all try one of the tricyclics like as to the next step Having a doctor who knows something about antidepressants can make a big My psychiatrist claims that most GPs and FPs don't have much experience in this area and from what I've seen I'm inclined to believe I think I know more about antidepressants than the people at my family practitioner's Disclaimer I'm not a doctor what I know about this comes from talking to my psychiatrist and reading John Werner UC Berkeley School of Education